OBX|3|TX|21828^Interpretation|1|See Ref Lab Comment |||U|||F
NTE|1||This individual DOES NOT have the Methylenetetrahydrofolate
NTE|2||reductase (MTHFR) C677T gene mutation. Although the MTHFR
NTE|3||C677T gene mutation is absent, the individual may have
NTE|4||other genetic or environmental risk factors for thrombosis.
NTE|5||The MTHFR C677T gene mutation test does not detect other
NTE|6||causes of hyperhomocysteinemia, such as occurs with other
NTE|7||mutations within the MTHFR gene or the Cystathionine beta-
NTE|8||synthase gene. In addition, the MTHFR C677T gene mutation
NTE|9||may not be present when hyperhomocysteinemia is due to
NTE|10||acquired disorders, such as deficiency of vitamins B12,
NTE|11||B6, or folic acid, chronic renal failure, zinc deficiency,
NTE|12||leukemia, psoriasis, or antifolate drug therapy. Consider
NTE|13||additional testing for hemostatic disorders associated with
NTE|14||increased thrombosis risk, if indicated.
